cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.MM

The paper deals with a problem of designing a dictionary for sparse representation of signals, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. The use of Bayesian methods and hierarchical priors is also a common approach in these fields. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision). The problem also involves information theory (cs.IT), signal processing (cs.SI), and multimedia (cs.MM), which are also possible sub-categories.
